- To install rails in our application 
```ruby
gem install rails 
```

- To create database files in rails
```ruby
rails db:create
```

- To open the console in the rails 
```ruby
rails console
```

- To generate scaffold in rails
```ruby
rails generate scaffold scaffold_name columname_1:datatype, columname_2:datatype,columnname_3:datatype,....,columnname_n:datatype
```

- when we create any data in seeds.rb file, To load all data from seeds.rb file to database we need to run the following command
```ruby
rails db:seed
```

- when we use any commands related to database or generate any data related to database then to commit them we use the following command 
```ruby
rails db:migrate
```

